* Certificates are not required - remove active generation, although keep the code.
* Only allow the app to run once; it hits an error about Indexed DB locking or similar, but that should be handled much more cleanly.
* When adding a competitor, need to be clearer that the team name is not prefixed (is a full name); could suggest "<club> 1" for the first one, but make it clearly a suggestion
* Remove spaces after club name in recording sheets (might have been an artifact of test; just do a trim regardless)
* Order of competitors in group matters:
   1. The Organizer cares some of the time e.g. do not put noob competitors on first, it'll freak them out.  They need to be able to construct that order (drag'n'drop or similar)
   2. The order is reflected on the scoring sheets *but* it rotates; the stated order is for the first apparatus, then on the second apparatus the first competitor moves to the bottom, and so on with each subsequent apparatus.
   3. However, on the programme it need only list groups and apparatus order for each group; everyone knows about the rotation.
* In prep, add ability to filter and sort by group
* Questions for users:
    * Should the results modal have national id and club in the left column?  It expands the display quite a bit (3 lines in worst cases), and another column makes it wider.  Does it add benefit, or is name enough?  It matches the recorder sheets, but that might not be worth the screen real-estate
* Can we edit the name of a competitor in the middle of a competition, e.g. we find a typo?
  * CUrrently have to delete/re-add, but also don't want a tight link from the Edit Known COmpetitors to competitions, becuase we shouldn't retcon past comps.  Maybe only current preparing comps?
* Teams comp (needed for Sept 2026): There is a special type of competition called a "Teams" competition.  Competitors are still in teams or not, but in this case:
  1. In announcments.pdf and places.pdf, only competitors *not* in a team have personal placings included; teams remain as is.
  2. In results.pdf, all competitors are listed, but it goes 'Teams', 'Team Members' (no unders/overs? TBC), then 'Individuals' (Unders/Overs)
